    "en": "A man said to him: 'I went out to Makkah, so a man accompanied me and he was my travel companion. When we were on one of the roads, he fell ill and became severely burdened. I used to take care of him. Then he regained consciousness to the extent that there was no problem with him in my estimation. When the day came in which he died, he regained consciousness, then died on that very day.'",
